When we tried to enter an order to use up that grant there were no delivery times available before May 27, because of the holiday weekend. We spoke with Charity in Partner Support and she told us to submit our order with a May 28 delivery day and then email you to get the deadline extended by a day. In addition to extending the deadline, please have your finance department deduct the order from the above mentioned grant. The computer automatically deducted it from our next MOCO grant which expires in June. I apologize for causing you extra work. Thank you for your assistance. Don't hesitate to call if you have any questions. Terry C: 240-793-5108

Summary: Status of delivery of Groceries to go order
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hello - We have not received our Grocery to Go Order as of 2:30 pm. It was supposed to be delivered by 2:00 pm. Please advise. If it is not coming a robo call needs to go out so all the seniors do not show up. Christal Batey On Feb 12, 2025, at 11:05'¯AM, partner Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: ï»¿ Good morning Partners, We hope this message finds you well. Today, February 12th 2025, the Capital Area Food Bank is operating solely in an administrative capacity, and there will be no deliveries or pickups due to the current weather conditions. For partners who have orders scheduled for tomorrow or Friday, we plan to operate under normal conditions. However, if you anticipate that your agency will be closed due to the weather, please reach out to Customer Relations as soon as possible to discuss rescheduling your order at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org or 202-644-9845. Additionally, even if your site remains open, we require confirmation that your location has been safely plowed and salted to allow for safe deliveries. If a driver arrives at your site and finds it is not adequately prepared, please be aware that your agency may incur a restocking fee. Our delivery equipment cannot navigate through snow or ice safely, and we prioritize the safety of both our drivers and your staff. We appreciate your cooperation and understanding as we work together to ensure everyone's safety during this weather event. We are actively monitoring the situation and will keep you updated with any changes regarding our operations for the rest of the week. Thank you for your partnership. Stay safe and warm! Best regards, Customer Relations

A NetSuite search identified SO158855 as the record with an outstanding balance. I updated ticket fields with the details. The order was placed today (4/28/2024). There was a grant applied but it did leave a 172.27 balance. I do not know how to look up which grant was applied and if there are still funds available to cover this balance. Brad [04/29/2024 07:47] Good afternoon, I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to inform you that you can only apply one grant to a single line item. Currently, you have a remaining balance of $30.17 on your 1-H grant, which the system is trying to use to cover the cost of your 300015 Macaroni & Cheese. If you order a line item that costs more than $30.17, you will still have a balance. However, if you would like to use your other grant, which has a larger balance and can cover the entire line item cost of $202.44, we can arrange that for you so that you won't have any remaining balance to pay for this sales order. Please let me know which grant you would like to use, and I will put in a ticket with my IT team to make the necessary changes. Thank you, Daniele [04/29/2024 07:52] Please use I-I to cover the balance. Do I have to order something for 30.17 to use that grant?{adf}{"type":"expand","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Doreen A. K Hines, Executive Director "},{"type":"hardBreak"},{"type":"text","text":"240-832-1039"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Living Legends Awards for "},{"type":"hardBreak"},{"type":"text","text":"Service to Humanity"}]}],"attrs":{"title":"Signature"}}{adf} [04/29/2024 08:10] Yes- you would need to order something that amount or less to use that grant and get the item covered, or it can still be applied; you will just have a balance afterward. You may order an item that is $50, and you will owe $20 afterward- in this case, the difference is larger so I will request that they use your larger grant. When this is complete I will let you know. [04/29/2024 09:51] The IT team has made this change. If you edit the order, it will revert back to the original coverage, so please let me know if you plan on editing it. [04/29/2024 01:24] I will probably not. [04/29/2024 08:53] Good evening, Your grants have been applied to cover the entirety of your order. You have no remaining balance due. Thank you, "D"

MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO190198 MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Chris Sent: Tuesday, January 7, 2025 12:25 PM Subject: EXTERNAL Important Update Regarding Your Orders CAUTION: This email originated from outside of the organization. Do not click links or open attachments unless you recognize the sender and know the content is safe Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO190198 MAIN CONTENT: Shirley Couteau Program Manager Hunger Prevention Center she/her/hers Office hours 7am - 5pm, Monday - Thursday703-441-8606 ext. 288 Leadership Prince William Class of 2023 ~ We Not Me Street Address: 3901 ACTS Lane Dumfries, VA Mailing Address PO Box 74 Dumfries, VA 22026 https: www.actspwc.org/ United Way #8001 CFC #21878 CVC #8118 I am

Once you complete the checkout process, your items are put on a sales order and finalized. The emails you receive are due to potential errors in our inventory or the pulling process that may cause changes to your order before delivery. This can happen for two main reasons. Firstly, if the pulling team finds that the item's quality is not up to our standards for delivery, it may be removed from your order or the quantity decreased. This can occur when partners place orders well in advance and by the time the order is picked, the item may no longer meet our quality standards. Secondly, if we run out of a certain product, this could be due to periodic inventory errors where the actual count of items doesn't match what's on the menu. While we strive to minimize these occurrences, we send email notifications to keep partners informed in case such changes are necessary before their order is fulfilled. Thank you, "D" [08/19/2024 03:58] Hi, makes sense. I received some side eye looks from those I love so much. I tried to explain the selection was slim, and that I believed it to be secure. Description:
REFERENCE NUMBERS:
Order Numbers: SO189116, SO189116

MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO189116 MAIN CONTENT: REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO189116 MAIN CONTENT: Taylor Allgood, MPA-SJ (She/Her) Student Support Coordinator, The Market https: www.american.edu/student-affairs/the-market.cfm
Custom field (Request Category): Orders - Pre delivery -> Data/Time Change - Reschedule
Merged Comments: [01/03/2025 10:39] !Outlook-ag0gk4so.png|thumbnail! [01/03/2025 12:51] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out to us! We have an inclement weather policy that can be found on PartnerLink. Typically, when inclement weather is forecasted, we urge our partners to contact us in advance, before the Capital Area Food Bank makes a decision about whether we will be open for the day. This way, we can help reschedule orders to a later date if possible. Please note that the Capital Area Food Bank does not follow government decisions regarding weather closures and delays. Our Operations Department and leadership team make decisions about our operating hours based on weather and road conditions to ensure the safety of our drivers and partners. The earliest time I can schedule your order is January 13th. Please let me know if you would like to reschedule your order, and I can take care of it on our end. Thank you again for reaching out! Best regards, "D" [01/05/2025 07:21] Good evening, Thank you for your response and for sharing the Capital Area Food Bankâ€™s inclement weather policy. I wanted to let you know that, as of 7:11 pm today, American University has officially closed for tomorrow, January 6, due to inclement weather. As a result, we will need to reschedule our order. The proposed date of Monday, January 13 (between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM if possible) works well for me if it aligns with your schedule. Please let me know if this time works on your end or if another adjustment is needed. Thank you for your understanding and flexibility. I look forward to hearing from you. [01/05/2025 07:25] Hello, I am sorry for the last-minute follow up. I just realized that on Monday, January 13, I am scheduled to attend CAFBâ€™s SNAP Enrollment Training from 11-1 pm. Seeing as though I will need to be present for the CAFB delivery, please let me know what other days and times next week may be available for delivery. If you have any openings on *Wednesday, January 15*, please let me know. Thank you! [01/07/2025 11:09] Good morning, I want to confirm that you spoke with a member of my team today. Your order has been rescheduled for tomorrow, depending on whether we are open. If there are any changes, we will keep you informed. Have a great day!

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Can you tell me the expiration dates on the donated items in my order? There were many items without pictures so it's difficult to know if they are appropriate for my site as well. I don't know the weight or size of each item. } ,"attrs": }
Custom field (Request Category): Menu -> Product Best By / Expiration Date
Merged Comments: [01/28/2025 10:41] [^SalesOrd_8531916.pdf] _(46 kB)_ [01/28/2025 12:09] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out about the expiration dates on your product. Unfortunately, we cannot provide specific expiration dates for these items. When a product is labeled as "assorted," it means it is a compilation of dozens of different products under that category that have been donated. These items are sorted by our volunteer teams or donated in bulk. While our volunteers are instructed not to include expired foods, items that are past their "best by" or "sell by" dates are considered acceptable for consumption and may still be included. We encourage all partners receiving these donated cases to be aware of this and to use the Food Coding Guide created by our Food Resources team and Nutrition Department. Additionally, we recommend using your knowledge of food safety and your senses (sight, smell, and texture) to determine if the food is in good condition. I apologize for not being able to provide further guidance on this matter. The nature of donated products, especially assorted bins, makes it difficult to pinpoint a specific expiration date for a mix of different items. [^Food Coding Guidance.pdf] Thank you, "D"

Regarding the tortillas, I apologize that they were sent out after their expiration date. I have reported this to the Food Resources Team for further investigation. However, since you received them, I have processed a credit of $45.60 for the tortillas you ordered (which had a discount applied). This credit will be applied to the invoice associated with your order, Invoice #180569. As for the flavored water, the date on the items indicated "BB," which stands for "best by." Many of our donated foods may be past their best by or sell by dates. These dates are intended to inform you of when the item is not at its peak quality, not about food safety. The items are still safe to consume, and we encourage our partners to use their judgment. Summary: Drivers are not able to see the special notes that are entered when order is placed
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hello, Of late, I am not getting a phone call letting me know that the driver is on their way to our Pantry. I enter a note for each of our orders asking that a driver call as they are leaving the warehouse so that our volunteers have enough time to get to our location when the truck arrives. We are a small organization - and our Pantry is just that - a large closet that stores a tremendous amount of food. We deliver our food to the clients so there is no 'office' available for volunteers to wait. When I scheduled today's delivery, a morning slot was not available. I had written asking if there would be any way to move our delivery up since we are normally an early delivery partner. I was told that the delivery schedule was full for the morning so that I had to keep my noon - 2 pm slot. I happened to be at the Pantry to do some stocking and the truck arrived at 10 AM! Luckily we were able to meet the driver with no delay to his schedule. I would appreciate it if drivers could please view the special notes/instructions for each delivery. I have been told by a few drivers that they do not see the special notes on their delivery receipt. Thank you for your help - Angela Harvey Pantry Manager, Bethesda Help
Merged Comments: [11/21/2024 12:05] Good afternoon, Angela, I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for your valuable feedback regarding our delivery process. I will connect with our Transportation Team to clarify the issue and explore ways to improve it. Each morning, our Transportation Leadership prints out the day's sales orders, which should include the notes you and your team leave. I will double-check to ensure this process is still in place, as we established a notes section specifically for partners to provide important information for our drivers. Additionally, I want to mention that there are times when drivers may finish their deliveries earlier than expected, or we may have more drivers available than anticipated. In such cases, drivers are instructed to call you to ask if you would like to receive your order before your scheduled delivery window. If you decline, they should wait until your designated delivery window. I will reach out to confirm these details and will follow up with you. I understand that the current situation is not ideal and the implications it has on your distribution. Best regards, "D" [11/21/2024 02:24] Good afternoon, Angela, I just spoke with Joe, the Transportation Manager. He informed me that he discussed the delivery process and the expectation for courtesy calls with the driver who made your delivery yesterday, as well as the team of drivers during their morning meeting today. Joe confirmed that drivers should be able to see the notes you leave on your sales orders. More importantly, it is mandatory for them to call all partners before their deliveries, even if they are within the designated delivery window. This call is to inform you that they are on their way. In instances where drivers can make earlier deliveries, they must consult with you first to see if you can accommodate the earlier arrival; if not, they are expected to wait until the agreed delivery window. If you continue to experience issues regarding this matter, please let me know, and I will arrange for Joe to give you a call to discuss it further. Best, "D"

Summary: Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Chris Sent: Tuesday, January 7, 2025 12:25 PM Subject: Important Update Regarding Your Orders Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations MAIN CONTENT: Hello - We would very much like to reschedule our Wednesday 1/8 delivery as soon as possible. Like many other of your partners, we rely almost exclusively on the food from CAFB. Our client demand is at its highest during the first 10 days of the month - so tomorrow's scheduled delivery is critical for our operations. Please let me know when our delivery can be rescheduled. Thank you for your continued support - and great work - Angela Harvey Pantry Manager, Bethesda Help ---- From: Chris (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) Sent: Tuesday, January 7, 2025 12:25 PM To: aeharvey1007@hotmail.com Subject: Important Update Regarding Your Orders Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations MAIN CONTENT: I sent this yesterday at 12:42 pm. I hope we are able to have today's delivery rescheduled to early next week. MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Than Sent: Friday, November 15, 2024 1:14 PM Subject: BPSOS - Delivery Issue Hello Alanna, This is Than from BPSOS. I am writing this to let you know about an issue with our food delivery this morning 11/15. We ordered a total of 8 or 9 pallets of vegetables this morning. However, those pallets were stacked on top of each other as a pair when they were delivered. We asked the driver if he could bring the pallets down since they are very heavy (about 800 lbs each) and our office did not have any equipment to handle that. He said that there was nothing he could do because they were loaded into the truck like that. We did have this issue in the past and it took our staff (which comprised of many seniors) a tremendous amount of effort to handle it. We always appreciate CAFB for providing the food for free, but in the future, it would be great if you do not stack pallets on top of each other. If you have no choice but to do so, please let us know in advance. Best, Than Tran Program Coordinator BPSOS, Inc 6066 Leesburg Pike, Suite 100 Falls Church, VA 22041 Phone: (703) 538-2190 Fax: (703) 538-2191 www.bpsos.org MAIN CONTENT: Alanna King (she/her) Partnership Specialist, VA Region Capital Area Food Bank P. 571.482.4773 | aking@capitalareafoodbank.org 6833 Hill Park Dr, Lorton, VA 22079 capitalareafoodbank.org Book time to meet with me

Let me look into this and I will get back to you.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} Thanks,{color} {color:#172B4D} Karen Alexander{color} ---- {color:#172B4D}{color} [11/19/2024 12:23] Good morning, Alanna, I apologize for the delay in my response! I hope you are doing well. This is feedback that we have received across the regions and I have communicated it to the Operations Teams for their awareness. For now, please relay the message below to the partner: _Good afternoon- The Customer Relations Team has reported your concerns to our Senior Managers in Operations, and they are committed to helping our partners address these challenges. They will be reviewing options to improve the situation moving forward. For the time being, items will continue to be packed as they are currently, but the team is looking into alternatives that would make unpacking easier for you and other agencies. I will keep you updated on any developments. I want to assure you that your feedback has been heard and is being taken into consideration. The reason for the current packing method is due to truck capacity. If the pallets are not stacked, they will take up more space in the truck and could potentially require multiple trucks for delivery. Our drivers carry pallet jacks with them on their routes, but they do not have reach machines like those used in the warehouse to pull orders and unstack items. We are working on this, and I apologize for the challenges it presents. Please reach out to patnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.orgwith with any concerns you may have._ Best regards, "D" [11/19/2024 12:24] [_partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org_|mailto:patnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]

MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Than Sent: Monday, November 25, 2024 10:06:59 AM Subject: BPSOS - Food Order Issue Hello Alanna, Happy Monday! This is Than from BPSOS. I am writing this because we encountered a technical issue on the website. Last Friday 11/22, we tried to add a few items, namely 2 of the 800908 Cabbage, Green Local 675# BIN 1/675 lbs Bin into our cart, to be delivered this Wednesday 11/27. However, it said that those items were not available on that selected date, but in the item description, it said that it will still be available until 12/10. As a result, we could not select those items back then. It was pretty late then, so I was not able to email you until today. I know that we may past the deadline for edit order; however, is it possible for you to remove all of the "300597 Turkey Breast, 6-9# Basted w/ Gravy Packet 1/30.42486 lbs Case" from our cart, and replace them with 2 of the "800908 Cabbage, Green Local 675# BIN 1/675 lbs Bin?" Additionally, do we still need to order more than 1000 lbs to be eligible for delivery? I know that we are asking a lot Alanna, but we want to make sure that our vulnerable and underserved population can enjoy a good Thanksgiving this week. We would appreciate a lot if you can help us. Best, MAIN CONTENT: Than Tran Program Coordinator BPSOS, Inc 6066 Leesburg Pike, Suite 100 Falls Church, VA 22041 Phone: (703) 538-2190 Fax: (703) 538-2191 www.bpsos.org If a federal employee or in the military, you can support our mission through CFC Charity No: 10038 CONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE: This email and any files transmitted with it are confidential and intended solely for the use of the individual or entity to which they are addressed. If you are not the intended recipient, you may not review, copy or distribute this message. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Grace Ferrara | MD Partnership Coordinator Capital Area Food Bank P. (202)-644-9824 gferrara @capitalareafoodbank.org 4900 Puerto Rico Ave NE Washington, DC 20017 Capitalareafoodbank.org
Merged Comments: [11/21/2024 12:08] !Outlook-A picture .png|thumbnail! !image.png|thumbnail! [11/25/2024 02:37] Good afternoon, Grace, I hope you are doing well. I wanted to bring this matter to Austin and discuss it with her. I understand the implications of the large orders and the concerns surrounding the removal of produce for the produce hub. When I spoke to Austin, she suggested that the first step should be to have a conversation with the partner to explain the implications of their edits to the order. They need to be mindful that they donâ€™t want to lose their produce items meant for the hub and that they should be aware of the weight of their orders when placing them. Here are two key points I discussed with Austin: 1. Currently, we do not have a formal limit for orders, so we cannot tell them what a limit would be. Operations and ERP/IT are working on measures to ensure that for large orders, the number of delivery blocks corresponds appropriately. For example, two weeks ago, Capital Christianâ€™s order required five trucks for delivery but only occupied one slot, which is unrealistic. For now, we can only ensure that Operations is aware and prepared for these situations. 2. Austin mentioned that if this situation continues to cause recurring issues and impacts the produce hub's participating sitesâ€”resulting in a loss of produceâ€”we can consider locking their orders for the produce hubs and requesting that they create a separate order. However, this could complicate matters since Operations has asked us to consolidate orders for the same partner to avoid having one sales order versus two. We can explore this locking option as a last resort if recurring issues continue. I hope this clarifies the situation, and please let me know if you need any assistance in engaging with the partner. Best, "D"

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Marie Sent: Thursday, August 15, 2024 4:23 PM Subject: Produce Hub Request Hi Augusta, I hope my email finds you well. I have a request about the Produce Hub: is it possible that the pallets of produce are not stacked on top of each other? SEED comes with a truck like the one from CAFB so it uses the pallet jack to pick up their produce but when the pallets are stacked on top of each other, we have no way to lower the pallet of produce which is on top which we forced to cut the cardboard, to extract the product into a bin so that another partner can have its product. If the pallets come individually, each organization has the possibility of collecting its pallet of produce to its truck. Also I looked at the order for the Hub but I only saw 50 squash boxes instead of 176 (the 58 boxes are the ones I ordered for my distribution). Will the rest be added later? Thank you Augusta Marie ODAH Administrative Assistant Coordinator of Food Pantry & Immigrant Resourcing Capital Christian Fellowship www.capitalchristian.org MAIN CONTENT: Good morning, Do you think the request not to stack could be adhered to? If so, I will put a note on their future produce hub orders. I am not sure who to loop in from ops, so please feel free to loop them in as needed. Thank you, Augusta From: Marie Odah Sent: Thursday, August 15, 2024 4:23 PM To: Augusta Fricke Subject: Produce Hub Request Hi Augusta, I hope my email finds you well. I have a request about the Produce Hub: is it possible that the pallets of produce are not stacked on top of each other? SEED comes with a truck like the one from CAFB so it uses the pallet jack to pick up their produce but when the pallets are stacked on top of each other, we have no way to lower the pallet of produce which is on top which we forced to cut the cardboard, to extract the product into a bin so that another partner can have its product. If the pallets come individually, each organization has the possibility of collecting its pallet of produce to its truck. Also I looked at the order for the Hub but I only saw 50 squash boxes instead of 176 (the 58 boxes are the ones I ordered for my distribution). Will the rest be added later? Thank you Augusta Marie ODAH Administrative Assistant Coordinator of Food Pantry & Immigrant Resourcing Capital Christian Fellowship www.capitalchristian.org|http: www.capitalchristian.org" _ _For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth on him should not perish, but have eternal life_ _ ." !~WRD0001.jpg|thumbnail! } ,"attrs": }
Merged Comments: [08/19/2024 09:39] !~WRD0001.jpg|thumbnail! [08/19/2024 09:39] Hi Augusta Fricke, Thank you for contacting the Capital Area Food Bankâ€™s Customer Relations Department! Our hours of operation between Memorial Day and Labor Day are Monday through Thursday, 8 a.m. to 5 p.m and Friday 8am to 3 p.m. We will respond to your request in a timely manner during business hours. You can expect a response by 10 a.m. the next business day for requests sent outside of business hours. Thank you, Customer Relations Capital Area Food Bank [08/19/2024 10:13] Good morning Augusta I will let "D" know about this feedback and this could be addressed during the inventory meeting tomorrow. I will let you know if I receive any updates CiArra [08/19/2024 02:07] Good afternoon, Thank you for submitting your request. I have forwarded this information to our Operations Teams so they can assist and provide a definitive answer on what can be done. Our Operations Team has specific reasons for the way pallets and trucks are packaged, in order to maximize truck space for loading your entire orders at once. I will update you as soon as I receive a response from the team. Thank you, "D" [08/19/2024 02:16] My request is only in the case of produce for the Hub because it facilitates the sharing between the different partners. Thank you in advance [08/21/2024 03:41] Good afternoon, Thank you again for bringing up this question. I have spoken to our Operations Manager in the DC warehouse, and unfortunately, we are unable to unstack or repack the pallets of produce in a different manner due to the truck's space capacity and efficiency reasons. Packing the pallets differently would require sending multiple trucks, causing inefficiency, and we also do not have the bandwidth to unstack and unpackage the cases and pallets of produce for each partner participating in the produce hub. One suggestion is that your agency acquire a pallet jack during the next round of capacity grants to assist with this issue. I will also pass this feedback on to the Operations Leadership team for consideration, but currently, our Operations Team cannot accommodate it under our current operating procedures. I apologize for this. Thanks, "D" [08/22/2024 09:23] Thank you so much for your explanation\! Be blessed! [08/22/2024 09:23] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.

Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click "verify" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. Regards, Godwin [08/28/2024 09:56] Good morning Godwin, I hope this message finds you well. I am writing in response to your recent produce requests, particularly your most recent message. I want to assure you that we do receive all of your produce requests. As we've mentioned before, we can only add produce that is available. Charity, the Customer Service Coordinator who has been assisting you, explained that we did not have any produce available on Monday. She assured you that she would monitor our inventory and add the produce to your order before it locks *if* it becomes available. Charity kept your ticket open and checked the menu regularly, but unfortunately, we did not have any produce to add to your order before it locked yesterday evening. I understand your frustration with this process, but please know that the produce we receive is put on the menu as soon as it is available. While my team supports partners by monitoring the menu, it would be best for you to also check the menu for updates. Unfortunately, we cannot add produce that is simply not available. I hope this provides some clarity. I also double-checked for any available produce before sending this message and saw that none was available. Thank you, "D" Manager of Customer Relations and Distribution Network Evolution (DNE) Â

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: We are by this mail request Capital Area Foodbank to include in our order for this month 100pcs of Turkey for Thanksgiving, whenever it is available. Our intention is to have our food give out on Saturday 23rd November 2024 by 12noon We thank you for your cooperation in this matter. Regards, Godwin Binutu For: CCC Covenant Parish. 2404678399
Merged Comments: [11/06/2024 02:35] Good afternoon Godwin, This year, our Food Procurement Team purchased two truckloads of turkeys, each at a cost of approximately $60 to $70 per case and were available on PartnerLink. These turkeys have been allocated to various orders and are no longer available. I reached out to my colleagues on the Food Resources Team, who informed me that we often receive donated turkeys. These donations will be provided at no cost now that the shared maintenance fee has been waived for donated items. _However_, *we cannot predict if and when these donations will arrive*. Typically, individuals and organizations tend to donate turkeys closer to Thanksgiving, usually in the week before the holiday or during the holiday week itself. Please continue to check the menu regularly to see if turkeys are added. If we do receive them, they will be added to the menu and available to partners on a first-come, first-served basis. Thank you, DH [11/07/2024 01:15] Dear Harmon. Thank you for your response. We buy Turkey every year from CAFB in bulk you can check your record. I think our organization should have been given some consideration during the sharing of 2 trucks load of Turkey. We don't rely on donations we buy our Turkey every year. We observed that since Elvis left we have been having issues inrespect of our order, this is very unfair. Our community are expecting thanksgiving Turkey from us only to disappoint them at the end. Regards, Godwin Binutu [11/07/2024 01:00] Good afternoon Godwin, I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for reaching out to me again regarding the turkey availability. I completely understand how important this is for your community, especially during the holidays. I want to clarify that all the turkeys we receive are available on a first come, first served basis for all our partners, just like other items on the menu. I also realize that in previous years, there was a fee associated with our donated turkeys (0.19 cents per pound). However, Iâ€™m pleased to share that this fee has been waived for this fiscal year, so itâ€™s possible you may have paid in the past but you would not have to this time for the donated product. I genuinely want to ensure that you and your clients receive the support you need this holiday season. I understand how quickly these items can disappear from the menu, and I encourage you to check it daily, as we frequently add new products. Right now, we also have vegetable oil, stuffing mix, corn muffin mix, canned collard greens, and beans that might help supplement your holiday distributions. Please feel free to check the menu regularly, and if I see any additional turkeys come available, I will reach out to you. Thank you for your understanding, and know that we are here to support you and your community during this important time. Warm regards, "D"{color:#4E8227}{color} !image001.png|thumbnail!{color:#4E8227}{color} *{color:#4E8227} *DH*{color}*{color:#4E8227}{color} {color:#4E8227}Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution{color}{color:#4E8227}{color} {color:#4E8227}Capital Area Food Bank{color}{color:#4E8227}{color} *{color:#4E8227} *P.*{color}*{color:#4E8227} 571.390.9875 | *F.* 703.541.0179{color}{color:#4E8227}{color} [{color:#0563C1}dharmon@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}|mailto:dharmon@capitalareafoodbank.org] {color:#3A7C22}4900 Puerto Rico Ave, NE Washington DC 20017{color}{color:#4E8227}{color}{color:windowtext}{color} !image002.png|thumbnail!{color:windowtext}{color} {color:windowtext}{color}!image003.png|thumbnail!{color:windowtext}{color} {color:windowtext}{color} !image004.png|thumbnail!{color:windowtext}{color} {color:windowtext}{color} !image005.png|thumbnail!{color:windowtext}{color} {color:red}Please email all customer service questions or concerns to{color} [{color:red} {color}{color:red} *partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org*{color}{color:red} {color}|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]{color:red} so that one of my colleagues or I can assist you promptly. Thank you!{color}{color:red}{color}{color:red}{color} [11/07/2024 01:26] Hello Godwin, Iâ€™m sorry to hear that you feel you havenâ€™t gotten the service you would like since there have been changes in staff. I would be happy to connect with you to discuss any challenges you are having. Regarding the turkeys, unfortunately, we donâ€™t have the capacity to track every partner that has received turkeys in the past, and it wouldnâ€™t be fair to our other partners to reserve inventory for a select few. However, there are times when we will receive a donation that is specifically allocated for the DC region. While this isnâ€™t a guarantee that we will receive such a donation, nor a promise to reserve anything, the regional team has made note of your interest and will notify you if we receive a special donation of turkeys for the region. As "D" mentioned, I also encourage you to continue checking PartnerLink so you will be aware as new items are added. Please let me know if you have any further questions for the DC regional team. Thank you for your continued partnership and the work you are doing to serve our community. Kindly, Lisa [01/10/2025 02:52] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out to us regarding the issues you encountered with your order. Our Return Policy, which is covered in our SMART Shopping Training, informs partners that any order discrepancies must be reported immediately. We provide partners with 24 hours for perishable items and 72 hours for non-perishable items to notify us about returns, exchanges, or any issues with their orders. We also encourage all partners to thoroughly review their orders upon delivery or pickup, so they can inform us about any discrepancies as soon as possible. I understand that circumstances, such as delivery day events, holidays, and our holiday and snow closures, can sometimes disrupt this process which can acount in the delay in notification. Unfortunately, since the items you did not order have already been distributed and we are now beyond the timeframe for reporting discrepancies, the original account balance you paid for the order remains unchanged. We sincerely apologize for the inconvenience this has caused your agency, especially regarding not receiving all the items you ordered. In the future, if you experience any issues like this, please contact my team, the Customer Relations Team, immediately via email at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]. This will automatically create a ticket for my team. You can also reach us at our shared phone number 202-644-9845. Thank you, DH Manager of Customer Relations and Distribution Network Evolution [01/13/2025 02:34] Thank you, "D", for your response. I am copying our food distribution team, and we will be sure to immediately report to your Customer Relations Team any discrepancies we may encounter in the future. REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO182764, SO182764, S9- MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Maria Sent: Wednesday, November 13, 2024 2:33 PM Subject: Order #SO182764 Hello Joanna, I just came back from vacation yesterday and was looking over our inventory to compose our guidelines for this week and noticed that the chicken that we received on Friday was not the TEFAP chicken that we had ordered for pick up on 11/08. It's on our team for not checking properly the case size and weight but the chicken which we received was the following: 300595 Chicken Leg Quarters, Halal 5# Chicken Leg Quarters, Halal 5# 6/5 lbs Bag We received 9 cases of the above chicken. I knew it wasn't correct based on the count and the fact that it was halal. I believe this is a purchase item through the CAFB website and wanted to check with you and the team to see how you would like to proceed. As a side note, on a past order we received 6 cases of TEFAP red kidney beans instead we had ordered 6 cases of TEFAP pears which was a minor problem and explained the importance of checking the order with our team prior to accepting. The information contained in this communication from maria.rodriguez@ccda.net REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO182764, S9- MAIN CONTENT: Thank you! Maria Rodriguez Pantry Manager Alexandria Food Pantry St. Lucy Food Project Catholic Charities of the Diocese of Arlington 4725A Eisenhower Ave. Alexandria, VA 22304 (703) 719- 8939 ccda.net

I appreciate your prompt reporting. We have informed our Operations Team about the matter, and they are currently calibrating our inventory to address it internally. Please follow Joanna's guidance on how to report only what you actually received. We will take care of the necessary items on our end. In the future, if similar instances occur, please make sure to review your order thoroughly upon delivery. If you notice any discrepancies, contact us immediately at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org so we can escalate the issue to our Operations Team as soon as possible. Thank you for your cooperation. Best regards, "D"

MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Emily Sent: Sunday, February 23, 2025 8:41 AM Subject: Damaged food Alanna We received a delivery of food on Tuesday, February 18. Everything was fine except for one case of peaches. 17 cans out of 24 in the case were damaged. I have pictures below. The cans with the black spots are holes where the juice leaked out. The two cans on paper had leaked and were stuck to the paper. You can see all the cans that were wet. We cannot give out food that is stained like this; plus, we have no way of knowing if the contents are bad. We could use only 7 cans from this box. Since prices are so much higher now and our money is tighter, we would like a refund. I have not heard anything about the cans of pears that were damaged a few weeks ago. Have a good week. Emily Emily Ewing West End Food Pantry. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use. Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: Get Help Map|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ . To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on September 19th from 9 am to 10 am . These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to register |https: forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations. Thank you, The Customer Relations Team
Merged Comments: [09/14/2024 02:39] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out! I have corrected this on our attendance log. Thank you! "D"

Summary: Inquiry about grant for vehicle for food pantry none
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Does CAFB assist with grants for transportation for food pantries? We are in need of a cargo van to transport food to our clients located in senior buildings and also to provide food on an emergency basis, which requires transporting the food to the client. If not able, can you provide resources and grant opportunities that cover non-profit organizations and transportation? Thank you, Janaclese Woods
Custom field (Request Category): Agency Administration -> Connection to CAFB Staff
Merged Comments: [09/16/2024 12:18] Good afternoon Partner, Thank you for your inquiry about Capacity Grants. We do indeed offer Capacity Grants at Capital Area Food Bank intended to help our partners expand their operations by providing financial assistance to cover the cost of items like storage or a vehicle. The Capacity Grant Application is embedded in our 2024 Fall Bi-Annual Survey, which will be released to partners in the second week of October. Please note that you will need to open and fill out the survey to access the Capacity Grant Application and then submit it. Once you submit your application, it will be reviewed by your Regional Team for consideration. Thank you, Customer Relations [09/16/2024 12:19] Please also reach out to your Regional Team Members to learn more about external grant opportunities that may be available for support.

Angela Wilson sent from my iPhone On Sep 13, 2024, at 3:37'¯PM, Customer Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: ï»¿ Good afternoon Partners, If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use. Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: Get Help Map|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ . To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on September 19th from 9 am to 10 am . These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to register |https: forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations. Thank you, The Customer Relations Team

Summary: Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hello Can you please cancel my order and I will do a new one. Thank you. Angela Wilson from Crossover Church. My order was for Wednesday Jan 8th at 10:00 am today. Angela Wilson sent from my iPhone On Jan 7, 2025, at 12:25'¯PM, Chris (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: ï»¿ Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations
Merged Comments: [01/08/2025 11:57] Good afternoon, Thank you for contacting Customer Relations. Your order has been canceled. "D"

Our Food Resourcing Team has informed me that this item is expected to remain in good condition until we return next week. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule. In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. CiArra [10/09/2024 11:12] Good morning, Unfortunately, we threw all the collard greens in the trash, I'd take pictures next time I see any bad produce before trashing. Please let me know if you need any other information. Thank you [10/09/2024 12:15] Good afternoon Thank you for contacting us about food item dates and quality issues. We want to ensure that all the food leaving our warehouse is safe for consumption and properly dated for your knowledge. Some of the items you mentioned are *donated products*. As we increase the donated products on our menu, I want to make sure that all partners are aware that Capital Area Food Bank accepts donations with items past their best by and sell by dates. The best by date is an indicator of the quality of a product but is not a safety date. The sell by date is for inventory management and tells the store for how long to display the product for sale. The product can still be consumed after this date. It's important to note that many of our donated products will be past these dates, but they are not expired and are still safe for consumption. We have food coding guides that partners can print and reference during distributions. When available, they can be ordered in English and Spanish from our Nutrition Education Department. The dates on some products may cause concerns for partners and their clients, but we urge you all to differentiate between the different dates on products, use the food coding guide as a reference, and also use your best judgment as well as your food safety knowledge. If you have a product that is not of the right consistency, has an odor, or you believe to be not okay, please let us know and discard the item immediately. As we increase our donations, we may encounter some challenges, but please work with us and continue to provide us with feedback. Additionally, if you ever have an issue with fresh produce, please include photos of the items so that we can forward them to our Operations and Food Resourcing Departments for their knowledge. We appreciate your partnership with us in this. For Nutrition Materials including the Food Coding Guide, please email: [education@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:education@capitalareafoodbank.org] [^Food Coding Guidance.pdf] "D"

MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Dear partner support coordinator, we at FBC Ken-Gar have grant allocations from 3 different grants, 2 of the expires in 30 days and the third expires in June. When we order food the funds are taken out of the grant that expires later. Is there any way that you could take the money from the accounts that expire first. It would be greatly appreciated. Thanks! FBC coordinator. , , , } } } ,"attrs": }
Merged Comments: [04/26/2024 03:49] Good afternoon, Thank you for contacting our Customer Service. I'd be happy to assist you with your query. Our system applies grants on a per-line-item basis, meaning only one grant can be applied to each line item. In your past couple of orders, you have had line items with high numbers ranging from $250 to $2,653.30. Â The system is going to use the grant that has enough available funds which might not be the one with the closest expiration date. Please see below: You have three grants: * 1-G $3,000 (Expires 1^st^) ** SO136067 used $890.00 ** SO122558 used $812.60 *** Remaining Balance: $514.98 * 1-H $2,378 (Expires 2^nd^) ** SO146902 used $762.58 ** SO142621 used $1,498.84 *** Remaining Balance: $116.58 * 1-I $6,564 (Expires 3^rd^) ** *SO157471 (your most recent order)* _was placed and totaled in $854.20, the only grant that could cover the entirety of this line item for the chicken was your 1-I grant. If the system pulled from either of your other two grants, it would not cover the total cost of the chicken._ I hope this clarifies the situation. If you have any more questions, please feel free to ask. Best regards, "D" [04/27/2024 01:24] Hi CONYANDLIZ@msn.com, This is an automated reminder from Capital Area Food Bank Customer Services. MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO192982, SO192982 MAIN CONTENT: REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO192982 MAIN CONTENT: Good morning. FISH of Laurel is so very happy to receive this $6006.85 grant as it has been many years since we have received a grant from CAFB! I have a question about invoice #194073 (this order' #SO192982 was received on 2/13; it was originally scheduled for delivery on 2/10, but there was a problem that day and the driver failed to arrive during the 8:00-10:00 AM delivery window). On 2/14, we received the following email: Dear FISH of Laurel, Inc., We are delighted to inform you that your organization has been awarded' grant' funding to support your efforts in addressing food security in our community.' $6,006.85 ' has been awarded to your organization under the new food credit' grant' '“' FY25 Maryland DHS' and the funds were made available in your account on' Monday,' February 10th, 2025. Partner food credits can be used by your organization to' purchase' grant' eligible items using CAFB's Partner Link Menu.' ' Your partner food credit' grant' deadline is May 15th, 2025. Please remember that the food credit' grant' deadline is applied to the delivery or pick up scheduled date, not the date you placed the order. CAFB reserves the right to change deadlines and to reallocate and/or extend' grant' deadlines based on partner usage to ensure contract requirements are being met. If your organization cannot use the full' grant' amount before the deadline, please tell us as soon as possible.' ' ' ' ' ' Are you able to apply the grant to this order? I believe that a number of items on this order are grant designated. Thanks. Linda
Merged Comments: [02/25/2025 11:24] Good morning, Thank you for contacting Customer Support. We have received your request, are looking into it, and will follow up with you shortly. Charity [02/25/2025 01:35] Good afternoon! Thank you for submitting your inquiry. I have contacted the Maryland Regional Team and reviewed the documentation provided for the grant. Unfortunately, the grant can only be applied to orders with a creation date after February 10th, which is when the funds were uploaded to your accounts. Therefore, we cannot apply the grant to any orders created before February 10th, even if they were delivered after that date. If you have any questions, please let me know. Best, "D" [02/25/2025 04:02] Thanks for the clarification, "D". Linda [02/25/2025 04:03] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.

MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO170804, SO170804 MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: April Sent: Thursday, August 29, 2024 2:49 PM Subject: Weevils Hi Riley, I hate to bother you with such a pesky problem but the Maseca we purchased on 8/6/2024 has a weevil infestation. I wanted you to be aware but I also want to make sure the remaining Maseca on the menu is pest free. We will need to replace our stock, should I find another source temporarily? !image001.png REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO170804 MAIN CONTENT: Hi All, We just got a report from a Virginia partner, Food For Others, that masa flour they received from us on 8/6 had weevils in it. Please use the troubleshooting tips listed below if you are experiencing any technical difficulties while on a desktop when editing your order * Clear your browserâ€™s cache.Â (If you do not know how to do this please Google how to clear the cache browser for Chrome * Restart your computer.Â * Try a different browser.Â * If you are on an iPad or tablet, please use a computer.Â Â * Update your computer/browser to the latest update.Â If you are still experiencing issues please let me know CiArra [01/17/2025 02:30] Ok, thank you.

Summary: Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders
Description:
REFERENCE NUMBERS:
Order Numbers: SO189181, SO189181, SO189181, SO189181

MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO189181, SO189181 MAIN CONTENT: REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO189181 MAIN CONTENT: Good day, I hope this finds you well. Is it possible to reschedule SO189181 For pickup this Friday, January 10, 2025? If not please cancel the order. Please confirm receipt. Thank you, Isha Lee 202-285-5354 Sent from my iPhone On Jan 7, 2025, at 12:25'¯PM, Chris (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: ï»¿ Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations
Custom field (Request Category): Orders - Pre delivery -> Data/Time Change - Reschedule
Merged Comments: [01/07/2025 04:12] Good afternoon, We hope this message finds you well and that you are staying safe in this weather! This is to confirm that your order SO189181will be picked up on Friday, January 10th, at 10am. Thank you, "D"

Summary: Re: Issue with Food Assistance Delivery from Gaithersburg HELP
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Ms. Jackson, Gaithersburg HELP is an all-volunteer organization that has been serving the needy in our local community for 56 years, and we are dedicated to supporting as many families with food each month as we can. In fact, last month HELP served 500 families at our pantry in the Festival Shopping Center. We have only a couple of volunteer drivers who can deliver food, and we must reserve that service for those individuals who live alone or have a partner who also can't drive to the pantry. You had asked for us to deliver food to a family of 9 people. As you must know from your previous food pickups, which total 30 since 2018, we pack according to family size; so a family of 9 would receive at least 8 heavy bags of groceries. We simply can't ask a volunteer, all of whom tend to be over 60 years of age, to pick up and deliver many bags of groceries; and that would not be appropriate when there are able-bodied family members in residence. As an all-volunteer organization, we strive to serve as many families as possible; but we can sustain our operation only if almost all of our families pick up at the pantry. If a client needs to come to the pantry via bus, we offer bus tokens so that transportation to and from the pantry is free. It is not an insult to let someone know that we have limited capabilities for food delivery. It's just a fact. And we would not ask to see proof of disability. We explain our limited delivery ability to any client who asks about delivery. Also, our coordinators always provide information about how to get food from Manna and/or the Gaithersburg Hope Center. Clients can get food from us while also getting food from those other organizations. In that way, we hope clients find they have more money to apply toward rent or utility bills. Our yearly client survey results validate that outcome and that our volunteers treat clients with dignity and promptness. We could serve your family very quickly with food if someone could drive to the pantry or come via bus. Margo On Thu, Nov 14, 2024 at 2:11'¯PM 'Yvette Jackson' via Info wrote: Dear Capital Area Food Bank Support Team, My name is Yvette Jackson, and I am writing to report an issue I experienced with food assistance delivery from Gaithersburg HELP. On Monday at 9:36 a.m., I called to apply for food assistance delivery, but my request was refused based on the number of people in my household and our ages. Specifically, this refusal has caused significant inconveniences and insult to my family and me, as we urgently need food assistance. Insulting my family by indicating "With such a large family someone should be able to take the bus here for pick up!" shows a lack of empathy and compassion. After making a complaint, I received a response at 12:54 p.m. today, indicating that the refusal and statement were correct due to the volunteer nature of the service and their inability to deliver help to a large household. I was directed to seek assistance from other sources such as Manna Food. I believe there might be a misunderstanding or miscommunication regarding our eligibility for this service. Attached to this email, you will find documentation of my disability for your review. Please note the MetroAccess document on line 16, which indicates that my disability prevents me from independently using the accessible Metrobus and Metrorail system for all trips. I am unable to walk due to L spine disease with a risk of falls, panic attacks, anxiety, and non-tolerance to crowds. At this point, I feel my disability, age, and household circumstances are severely limiting my access to essential help. I would appreciate your assistance in reviewing this matter and providing any necessary support to ensure that my household can receive the food assistance we need as it appears Gaithersburg Help is not completely meeting the needs of the community. I value your prompt attention to this issue and look forward to your response. Ms. Yvette L. Jackson| Ladean_29@yahoo.com| 240/937-7403| , , , , } } } ,"attrs": }

Just so you are aware, working doesn't automatically mean someone is able-bodied. "Able-bodied" typically refers to a person who has no physical disabilities and can perform tasks without any limitations caused by a disability. Many people with disabilities or health conditions can still work, often with the help of accommodations or support. So, just because someone has a job, it doesn't necessarily mean they don't have a disability. It's important to look at each person's unique situation and disabilities which you have indicated is not asked. Thank you for your response. Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Will you sell turkeys this year for Thanksgiving?
Merged Comments: [11/14/2024 12:40] Thank you for inquiring about the availability of turkeys. With Thanksgiving and the holiday season approaching, we understand the demand for turkeys from our clients and partners. We have two trucks scheduled that arrived in early October with purchased turkeys available on a first-come, first-served basis. Please note that these turkeys will not be free and will have associated costs. Donated turkeys are traditionally received closer to Thanksgiving. If our Food Resource Team is able to procure additional turkeys, they will also be available for purchase on a first-come, first-served basis. *Customer Service cannot reserve or allocate turkeys for any partner.* If you are looking for alternative sources of turkey offerings or region-specific turkey donations, we recommend reaching out to your Regional Team. It's important to note that Customer Service will *not* be involved in the allocation of turkeys. All turkeys, unless already pre-planned for, will be available on a first-come, first-served basis through PartnerLink. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation. CiArra [11/14/2024 02:08] Hello, See email below. Who is our regional team so that I can contact them regarding Turkeys. [11/14/2024 02:08] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved. [11/14/2024 02:58] The coordinator for DC is Erin Brown [ebrown@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:ebrown@capitalareafoodbank.org] +12027695614

Merged Comments: [06/17/2024 08:48] !IMG_20240617_083143.jpg|thumbnail! !IMG_20240617_083149.jpg|thumbnail! !Screenshot_20240617-083919.png|thumbnail! [06/17/2024 08:48] Hi drey_v27@yahoo.com, We just received your request for assistance. We will reply as soon as possible. Thank you, Customer Relations Capital Area Food Bank [06/17/2024 12:07] Good afternoon, Thank you for contacting customer support. I am looking into the dates for your previous orders to confirm that they are safe to eat. As a reference, feel free to use our Food Coding Guide (attached) as a resource when navigating different dates. I will follow up with you as soon as I get updates regarding the products you asked about. [^Date Coding Guide.pdf] Charity [06/26/2024 04:51] Hi Andrea, I hope you are doing well. I wanted to talk to you about the ticket you submitted. I apologize for the delay. One of my team members brought up your concerns regarding some items you received from us. After discussing your concerns about the salad dressing with my management and the Food Sourcing Team responsible for all the food that comes into the Food Bank, here are some points I wanted to share with you. Regarding the salad dressing, our Food Resourcing Team does not have a specific recommendation for shelf-stable milk or salad dressing in our Food Coding Guide. We suggest following the USDA's recommendation regarding this product specifically and apologize for not being able to provide further insight. Partners and clients should use their eyes, noses, and, taste buds to determine if a food is spoiled and therefore unsafe to eat. Of course, if a product is showing any signs of spoilage such as rot, mold, foul odor, etc., we will accept a return. I have brought this issue to management's attention, and I agree that our Food Coding Guide needs improvement. I will raise this with our leadership for further review. In response to your second point, I acknowledge the importance of best-by dates for our partners and their clients. However, our team faces challenges in obtaining these dates for donated products. One challenge arises during packing events when volunteers check and pack donated items into cases labeled as assorted on the menu. These assorted cases contain items from various donors and are packed without specific best-by date information for each individual product. Another challenge occurs when we receive donated products in different case lots-with different dates, making it difficult to provide accurate best-by dates to our partners. We don't know what case lot your order is going to be pulled from until its pulled the day before or two before its delivered or picked up. Although we practice FIFO (first in, first out) inventory management, the dynamic nature of our inventory makes it challenging to predict best-by dates with certainty. As our inventory of donated products increases, we are committed to improving our processes to provide partners with the information they need to make informed decisions. We are continuously seeking ways to improve our processes, and I encourage partners to participate in the upcoming Partner meetings in July to address any questions or recommendations regarding product dates. Thank you for bringing these concerns to our attention. Warm regards, "D"

MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: Sent: Thu, Aug 15, 2024 at 4:51 PM Subject: Item removed from order Hello, i just saw that item 100757 was removed from our delivery tomorrow. It is a pallet of meals to go that we were going to offer our clients as back to school choice. We were planning giving at least 2-3 per family. Right now we are going to end up giving 1 per family. It is disappointing. I dropped the other individual cases and decided on a pallet thinking that surely CAFB knows how many full pallets they have of an item since it is large and there are only 15 posted (at least when I initially saw it). It is even more disappointing because every week it seems as though an item is being removed from our order. This week it is a full pallet of meals to go. Last week it was 6 cases of eggs, and 3 weeks ago a bin or corn. I thought that when the number of items get posted to Partner Link, these are the number of items available to order. I am trying to understand why the items are missing by the time items get pulled. And it should not be happening almost every week. I have the same pallet ordered for delivery date 8/23. Am I going to assume that item is also gone since the same item is now not available or missing? We appreciate what you all do but there is always room for improvement. Thank you for your time and help. I wanted to write to you regarding the missing items list. I have been in communication with our Operations Department about the issue with your order. After searching the warehouse and conducting some internal inventory recalculations, we have identified inventory errors and mispicking for this order. A few weeks ago, we communicated to all our agency partners about the challenges we have been facing with inventory and operations. We acknowledge the impact this has on our partners and their distributions. We are working internally to address this issue by conducting more inventory calibration and providing additional training for our staff to improve accuracy in our Operations Department. Unfortunately, these items cannot be redelivered as we no longer have them. I understand this is frustrating and have reported this incident, as well as others from our partners, to my leadership. We are dedicated to improving your experience with us and want to ensure you have a better experience. Please accept our apology. [10/28/2024 01:30] Hi Andrea, I spoke to the Regional Coordinators and below is the itnel that they had to share about this topic: _Partners cannot require clients to volunteer in exchange for food. Since you are using Service Insights, the partners will need to create a client profile for the volunteer in the same manner as they do for all clients._ _Volunteers have the same access to food as clients. MAIN CONTENT:
REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: S2 MAIN CONTENT: REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: S2 MAIN CONTENT: Good morning, This past Friday the delivery driver told one of our Pastors that he can't wait until 10 am and the pastor had to receive the order. Summary: Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hello - I would like to reschedule the Jan. 8 delivery to the following Wednesday, Jan. 15. Either the 8-10 am or the 10-12pm delivery window is acceptable. Please confirm so I can have the volunteers on hand. Thank you, Kristine Hesse Grace Episcopal Church On Tue, Jan 7, 2025 at 12:25'¯PM Chris ( partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org ) wrote: Good morning, Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th. We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations. We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it. Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( 5 pm ) on January 7th , or the order will be canceled on our end. Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further! We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule. Warm regards, Customer Relations
Custom field (Request Category): Orders - Pre delivery -> Data/Time Change - Reschedule
Merged Comments: [01/07/2025 04:28] Good afternoon, We hope this message finds you well and that you are staying safe in this weather! This is to confirm that your order SO189313 has been rescheduled to Wednesday, January 15th, from 8 a.m. to 10 a.m. "D"
