Merged Comments: [09/30/2024 04:08] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called "Hours of Operations" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled "Hours of Operations." Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click "verify" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. Screenshots have been included to provide visual guidance (They are examples not for your agency). If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours|https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours|smart-link] Thank you, CiArra !Image20240926120623.png|width=571,height=206,alt="Image20240926120623.png"! !Image20240926120630.png|width=589,height=134,alt="Image20240926120630.png"!

Summary: Unavailability of Fruit & Vegetables in Cases
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hi Partner Support, We were told that cases of fresh vegetables would be available some time ago. They are never available when we're placing our orders. So, does that mean they are really never going to be available anymore for small sites with no dock availabilty? We have not been able to pick up fresh vegetables since Covid began and in-house shopping was discontinued. Your positive response would be appreciated. MaryAnn Tolbert
Merged Comments: [01/06/2025 08:14] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out to Customer Relations. I appreciate your inquiry. We offer a variety of fruits and vegetables on our menu throughout the week, but the selection can vary depending on seasonal availability. During the winter months, for example, we typically have fewer options compared to the summer when a wider variety of produce is available. In recent weeks, the fruits and vegetables available have primarily included potatoes, apples, and carrots. Due to producelimitations placed on agencies, our Food Resources Team is working to bring in more produce items in case lot instead of large bins and full pallets, but this remains an ongoing challenge. Currently, all produce items must be ordered through PartnerLink, as there are no plans to reopen the agency mart for direct pickups. I have two suggestions to enhance your experience in this situation. First, you can place orders up to 10 days in advance of your scheduled pickup and delivery date. I recommend placing your order as soon as the calendar opens and frequently checking PartnerLink for available produce. You can edit and add to your order until it locks for fulfillment, which is three business days prior to the shipment date. This flexibility allows you to include any additional items you may find during that 10-day window. Another option is to explore our TEFAP program, a government-subsidized initiative through which participating partners can access additional items to supplement their regular orders. Please note that this program has specific requirements and is managed by the TEFAP team. For more information, you can reach out to Zaynab, the DC TEFAP coordinator: [zkadhem@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:zkadhem@capitalareafoodbank.org] Thank you! Best regards, "D"

Thank you, Samantha Stevens On Fri, Sep 13, 2024 at 2:37'¯PM Customer Support ( partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org ) wrote: Good afternoon Partners, If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use. Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: Get Help Map|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ . To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on September 19th from 9 am to 10 am . These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to register |https: forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations. Thank you, The Customer Relations Team

Custom field (Request Category): Partner Produce Limit -> Question or Concern
Merged Comments: [12/19/2024 03:07] Good afternoon, Marie, I hope you are doing well. Thank you for your question. Yes, our Food Resources team, which is responsible for procuring food, including produce items at the Food Bank, was very much involved in the conversation and collaboration regarding the produce limits. One of their initiatives is to start procuring cases for our smaller agencies that have produce limits under 2,000 lbs. I also want to remind you that if you see a pallet of, for example, 2,000 lbs, the system will allow you to order over your limit. Customer Service will then reach out to you to discuss your options. If that is the only item available at that time and no cases are offered, we will permit the overage as long as it is not excessive. Best, "D" [12/19/2024 03:59] Thank you.

Could you please forward the response below on my behalf? Thank you! ---- Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. You had a great question about our recall process. For our DDP programs (mobile and community markets), the recall outreach process differs from that of the partnership teams. When a recall is identified, our Food Resources, Analytics, and Operations Teams collaborate with our programs and my team (Customer Relations) to contact the partners who ordered the affected items. It is then the partners' responsibility to reach out to their clients. For DDP, the process is slightly different. I recommend contacting Jessica Arias, one of our managers on the DDP team, to learn more about how they notify their sites and assist those sites in informing their respective clients. Thank you, CR [10/01/2024 08:08] Good afternoon, Thank you for your message to our team and for your patience while we look into this matter. I apologize for the issues with your two orders. Regarding the Produce Boxes, we have contacted your Regional Coordinators, Grace and Augusta, and they will communicate with Coastalâ€™s Customer Service Team to address the problem with your produce boxes that were not distributable. Augusta has offered to follow up with them and relay any next steps back to you. As for the peanut butter, thank you for providing photos. We appreciate it. The peanut butter in your order, as well as many of our other donated items, have passed their "best by" date. This date indicates when the product will be at its best flavor or quality and is not a safety date. Itâ€™s a quality date that encourages consumers to eat food while it is in its prime state. Food that is past this date is not bad and should not be thrown away. We provide a food coding guide to our partners that explains these dates further. We want to reassure you that the peanut butter is not expired and will not cause any harm to consumers. We offer the Food Coding Guides as a resource and we have them printed and available to order for partners as well to pass out at distributions. [^Food Coding Guidance.pdf] Thank you, "D"

Merged Comments: [04/25/2024 04:57] Good afternoon, Thank you for contacting our Customer Service. I'd be happy to assist you with your query. Our system applies grants on a per-line-item basis, which means that only one grant can be applied to each line item. In the case of your order, the line item is $817.00, and the system initially used the last of your FY24 MD Region Moco 1-G grant, which was $75.59. However, as per your request, I have contacted our IT department to apply your FY24 MD Region MOCO 1-I grant to that line item since it is the only grant you have that can cover the entire amount. Please note that moving forward, the $75.59 remaining on your 1-G grant and the $18.01 left on your 1-H grant may not cover the entire line item cost. If this happens, it is because our system applies the grants on a per-line-item basis. If you have a line item that costs less than these amounts in future orders, then you will have no remaining balance. I hope this clarifies the situation. If you have any more questions, please feel free to ask. Best regards, "D" [04/25/2024 05:03] Do you plan on making any further changes to this order? Summary: Why have there been no new items (including produce) added to the shopping menu in almost 2 weeks?
Merged Comments: [07/03/2024 09:35] Hi mjohns6439@gmail.com, We just received your request for assistance. We will reply as soon as possible. Thank you, Customer Relations Capital Area Food Bank [07/03/2024 11:10] Good morning, Thank you for your questions about the limited items on the menu. While I don't have a general answer, there are several factors at play. Firstly, at certain times of the year, we have constraints on our receiving calendar, which leads to fewer inventory trucks due to scheduling conflicts. Currently, we are facing this situation as we were closed for Juneteenth, went through our bi-annual inventory last week, and will also be closed for the July 4th observance next week. Additionally, as we prepare for our move back to home building in the Virginia region, there may be a slight shift in the amount of products as we transition inventory from one location to another. This means we have been and will continue to receive fewer trucks than usual and are trying to schedule loads that fit within this restricted schedule. Moreover, while donations vary, we are actively working to increase the amount of donated food we receive and make it available through our Partner Direct Program and the menu. This issue will be discussed in an upcoming in-person partner meeting in July, giving partners the opportunity to hear from our leadership and our Food Resourcing Team, who are responsible for sourcing all the food on the menu, both donated and purchased. Let me know if you have any further questions or concerns. Thanks, "D"

If I did something wrong, I'd like to know so I don't repeat it. Marian Sent from my iPhone On Nov 25, 2024, at 8:04 PM, partner Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: ï»¿ Dear Valued Partner, We regret to inform you that we had to remove or reduce the quantity of item(s) from your order SO183847 . Below is a list of item(s) and reason for the change. We understand that this change may cause inconvenience to you and your distribution plans, and we apologize for the inconvenience. Please note that if you are receiving this notification after your order has been locked, which is three business days before your order is due to be picked up or delivered, this change is most likely occurring during or after the pulling stage and unfortunately, we cannot replace the item removed or make any further additions during this time period. ||Item ||Reason for Change | |300595 Chicken Leg Quarters, Halal 5# |Line Not Fulfilled in WH | |800068 Peppers, Bell 25# CASE |Ordering Error | To review an updated version of your order, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History tab. If you have any queries or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org Thank you for your understanding and continued support. Best regards, Partner Support
Merged Comments: [11/26/2024 08:14] Good morning, Thank you for reaching out to us about this! You did not do anything wrong. An "order issue" means that we ordered this product from a farmer or vendor, and something went wrong with our order. For example, they may have been scheduled to deliver it one week but informed us they couldn't come until the following week, or they told us we were supposed to receive 10 cases but only delivered 6. Rest assured, this is not your fault! Best, "D"

[09/10/2024 09:59] Hey Erin, I just spoke with the partner and confirmed all of the quantities with them and they said theyâ€™d like to keep them as is and will distribute multiples to clients CiArra [09/10/2024 10:07] [~accountid:641358c50152b5f4f9f0b9d3] is that okay from a TEFAP regulations perspective? [09/10/2024 10:17] There are no regulations limiting how much a partner can order, but I really do not think these quantities are reasonable. [02/21/2025 09:48] Good morning Jeanette, I hope youâ€™re doing well today. I was very concerned to hear about the issues youâ€™ve encountered with mice droppings and the presence of mice near the food you received from us. Please know that I am genuinely sorry for this distressing experience, and I want to extend my heartfelt apologies on behalf of Capital Area Food Bank and our Customer Service and Operations Team. This morning, I forwarded the information you provided in your ticket, along with your photos, to our Director of Operations. She is taking this matter very seriously and has scheduled a meeting with her team to ensure we find a prompt and effective resolution. They will be focusing on maintaining cleanliness and ensuring rodent protection in our facilities, as well as inspecting our warehouse products, particularly those in question, to ensure they are removed if necessary. I want to support you through this situation. Could you please let me know which specific products you needed to be disposed of due to the potential rodent issue, aside from the bins of cereal? I understand how disruptive this can be to your food distribution efforts, and I truly empathize with the challenges it presents in providing safe and healthy food to the community you serve. I will also reach out to my supervisor to discuss possible compensation for the inconvenience caused by this situation, as we value your partnership and want to make things right. Thank you for your understanding, and once again, Iâ€™m truly sorry for the trouble this has caused. We are committed to resolving this matter as quickly as possible. Best wishes, "D" [02/25/2025 08:11] {color:#172B4D}Dear "D",{color} {color:#172B4D} Thank you so much for your prompt response and for addressing this matter with great regard. Instead, we used the time to do a deep cleaning to ensure all our 800 Rx Boxes are safe.{color} * {color:#172B4D}We also use two additional days of work to contain and capture the three mice and safely throw the 2 bins of assorted cereals out of our building premises (into a landfill). Strengthening our inspection processes to ensure that all pullers, drivers, and inspectors thoroughly check every order once it's staged. 4. I truly empathize with the impact this situation may have had on your operations, and I want to assure you that we are committed to providing a better service moving forward. Please know that we value your partnership and appreciate your understanding during this time. As a gesture of goodwill, we would like to waive the delivery fees for both your recent order and your upcoming order on March 3rd. REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO160977 MAIN CONTENT: EMAIL HEADERS: From: Partner Sent: Monday, May 13, 2024 4:10 PM Subject: Memorial Day 5/27 Dear Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused. Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule. In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding. Thank you for your patience and cooperation. Sincerely, Partner Support !image001.png REFERENCE NUMBERS: Order Numbers: SO160977 MAIN CONTENT: Jeannette Mendy Community Pantry Director LindaBen Foundation Inc. However I found it again available to order, same quantity, on Sunday evening, 1/26/25. I added it again, same quantity, to my next order SO191941. Could you please let me know why it was removed from my order? You can find a guide in PDF format called "Hours of Operations" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation.[^Updating Hours of Operations (Partner Facing Document).pdf] Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled "Hours of Operations." Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click "verify" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. !image-20240924-183113.png|width=981,height=223,alt="image-20240924-183113.png"! !image-20240924-183122.png|width=951,height=344,alt="image-20240924-183122.png"! Summary: There is a note on the order page about verifying hours or account will be locked. What does that mean and what needs to happen?
Merged Comments: [09/25/2024 06:40] Thank you for your inquiry on our Hours of Operations Feature on PartnerLink. We encouraged all partners to attend one of the four trainings that we hosted between August and September to ensure that everyone was well-equipped to utilize this feature effectively. This feature is crucial for maintaining accurate information about your agency's operating hours, which in turn updates our [Get Help Map|https://www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/] on the website. The Get Help Map is a tool that clients use to locate nearby CAFB Partners, so it's essential to have the correct hours displayed. If you were unable to attend the trainings, don't worry. There are alternative options available, such as accessing the resource on PartnerLink under the Partner Resources tab, or signing up for [Customer Relations Office Hours|https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours] held every Wednesday from 10am-11am. Please note that due to the nature of the training, there are no recordings or slides available, as it involved a live demo and Q&A session. While partners are not being reprimanded for not attending a training, it's important to highlight that starting *October 1st*, partners who have not updated or confirmed their hours will see a banner prompting them to do so before placing an order. You will need to take this action to proceed with making an order. If your hours have not changed, simply verify them by accessing the Agency Overview section after clicking your agency name on PartnerLink. If changes are necessary, please update them accordingly. For further assistance, please contact us at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]. [09/25/2024 08:16] So I went and clicked verify. Are we good now? Thanks, Jeff [09/26/2024 08:44] Yes, you are good. In the future, when you receive requests for updates, your account is not locked; it is simply asking for you to verify your information before you can proceed with placing an order. Have a great day! "D"

There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use. Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: Get Help Map|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ . To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on September 19th from 9 am to 10 am . Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to register |https: forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations. Thank you, The Customer Relations Team

Summary: Inclement weather policies link sends me to 2024 Holidays.pdf
Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hi, I am expecting a delivery on Monday January 6th, and there is snow in the forecast. I was hoping to review your inclement weather policies, and the link sends me to 2024 Holidays.pdf. Would you please let me know what will happen if it snows and what do I need to do? Thank you and Happy New Year! Luanne Ailes Messiah UMC 703-927-7913
Merged Comments: [01/01/2025 11:22] Good morning, Luanne, Happy New Year! I hope you had a great holiday. I have attached our Inclement Weather Policy below. [^Inclement Weather Policy.pdf] In the event that it snows, we will wait for information from our leadership, including the Head of Operations, to determine if we will have a formal delay or closure - we do not follow the governmentâ€™s decisions regarding weather. For example, if we announce a 2-hour delay, all delivery and pickup windows will be pushed back accordingly. This means that if you had an 8 AM - 10 AM delivery, it will now be scheduled for 10 AM - 12 PM. If we face a complete closure due to the weather, there will be no deliveries or pickups. On such days, the Customer Relations team will be available to reschedule deliveries and reach out to all partners regarding their orders. Additionally, please keep in mind that depending on the amount of snow, there may be impacts on the days following the snowfall. If we do have a closure, we will do our best to accommodate our partners' schedules while ensuring that orders are not affected the following day. I hope this helps! Please let me know if you need any further information. Best, "D" [01/02/2025 09:11] Thank you, "D"! Luanne

Merged Comments: [01/16/2025 11:55] Good morning, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out from the Customer Relations Team here at Capital Area Food Bank. We are contacting you to inform you that you have exceeded your produce limit by 1,750lbs. At this time, no action is needed and no removals are required; this message is simply to notify you of the overage. Thank you, Customer Relations [01/17/2025 11:30] Good Morning, I am confused by your message and unsure of its meaning and impact on current and future requests. Will the pallet that I recently ordered be delivered on the requested date, January 23rd. Does the weight prevent me from ordering in the future? Please advise. Paula Porter Metropolitan Baptist Church [01/17/2025 11:30] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved. [01/17/2025 12:15] Good morning, I am happy to provide further insight. The pallet you ordered will not be removed from your order and will be delivered on the 21st. However, this pallet has exceeded your agencyâ€™s produce limit of *250lbs*. At this time, due to the transition of implementing produce limits, we are not removing any produce from orders even if it exceeds their limit to allow partners to adjust. Once partners are more familiar of this process, we will begin adjusting orders, in communication with you, to have your orders align closer to your monthly allotted poundage. You are able to continue submitting orders as your agency allows, but for the rest of this or any month, you will no longer be eligible to order more produce once the limit has been met or exceeded. Please reach out to your Regional Team should you feel like an adjustment would be most beneficial for your agency. Hope this helps! I received my CAFB confirmation email yesterday and it reflects pickup. Please advise if I need to take any further steps to ensure delivery. Thank you so much for all your support. Sincerely, Paula Porter We Are One Body Food Pantry Metropolitan Baptist Church

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Good Morning,_x000D_ _x000D_ The delivery was made today by Mr. Ebenezer. However, he refused to pick up the empty pallets. He's the first driver who has not done this on the day of delivery. Could you please send someone to pick them up? Our space is very limited, and we don't have room for the empty pallets of last week. I also made a mistake when signing the order, and he was very upset. _x000D_ _x000D_ Thank you,_x000D_ Matilde Alvarado_x000D_ Mother of Light Center_x000D_ _x000D_ Sent from my iPhone
Merged Comments: [10/01/2024 10:13] Good morning Mitilde, I hope you are doing well. Thank you for sharing your feedback with us; it is very valuable. I will follow up with the Transportation Leadership Team to address the way the drivers communicate with partners about this issue. To provide some context, there are two main reasons why drivers may not take pallets when dropping off food during a delivery. Firstly, they may have food for an immediate order or need to pick up food from another site for the warehouse, which means they cannot have food and pallets on the truck at the same time due to food safety (Pallets are often leftoutside- on the ground, possibly in the rain, and are often dirty) and consideration for our partners. Secondly, our drivers may be on tight schedules and do not have the time for a pallet pickup due to their busy delivery schedules, especially during the busy season. There is no reason why a driver could not explain this to you at the time, and I will ensure that this information is communicated to them. I apologize for your experience. Thank you, "D" [10/01/2024 10:21] I spoke with the Transportation Supervisor, and she mentioned that she received feedback about the pallets not being stacked properly and having trash around them. She has scheduled a pallet pickup for tomorrow. Please make sure that the pallets are stacked together to allow the equipment to pick them up easily, there is no debris around them, and they are placed on concrete, not on grass. Thank you! [10/01/2024 10:43] !image3.jpeg|thumbnail! This is how the pallets were placed. We canâ€™t stack them any higher, so we have to put them to the side due to our limited space. The driver was rude, which is unusual, as weâ€™ve always had great relationships with all the other drivers. Thanks for picking the pallets soon. This ensures that we have the most up-to-date information in our internal systems and for clients to utilize. As a reminder, once approved, the information we gather from your updates will be linked to the information provided in our online tool that clients can use to locate food assistance: Get Help Map.|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ | | 'Š | | To ensure that all partners understand how to utilize this function, we will host four training sessions: two in August and two in September. Merged Comments: [10/02/2024 09:09] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called "Hours of Operations" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled "Hours of Operations." Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click "verify" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. !image-20240924-183113.png|width=981,height=223,alt="image-20240924-183113.png"! !image-20240924-183122.png|width=951,height=344,alt="image-20240924-183122.png"! Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hi team, I hope you are doing well! I recently learned that partners are being charged for orders that are mixed TEFAP and non-TEFAP. I double checked with the states, and no cost can be associated with TEFAP, even if there are other items included. Can you please remove the associated charge, and let me know if you have questions or concerns before moving forward. Austin, just including you as an FYI. Thanks! Alexis
Merged Comments: [01/03/2025 01:20] Good morning, Alexis, I hope this message finds you well, and Happy New Year! Thank you for providing this important information; it is definitely something we need to note. To give you some background, partners have been charged delivery fees for orders that include a mix of TEFAP products and other donated or purchased items for some time. As stated in our SMART Shopping Policy, orders that contain only TEFAP products do not incur a delivery fee. However, orders that mix TEFAP with purchased or donated products do have a delivery fee associated with them. I do not have the ability to remove delivery fees from all orders, as these fees are automatically added when partners place their orders. I believe we will need to submit an ERP ticket to stop this charge permanently, as it is an automated process. To clarify what the ticket would entail: Are we asking for no delivery fees to be applied to any orders containing any TEFAP items for al regions? Additionally, will we need to issue refunds for past orders that were charged delivery fees due to the mix of TEFAP and other products? I anticipate that partners will inquire about previous orders that included these fees as we proceed with this change and it also may be a good idea to plan for a formal communication to TEFAP partners since this is a change in poliy that we have previously stated to them. Is there a deadline for when this needs to be implemented? I understand that it should be done as soon as possible, but any changes/refunds to delivery fees are always approved by Austin, who is currently out until January 9th. Thank you for bringing this matter back to our attention again, hope to resolve this as soon as possible! Best, "D" [01/03/2025 05:19] Hey "D", happy new year and thanks for your response! Yes, weâ€™re asking for no delivery fees to be applied to any orders containing any TEFAP items for al regions. But, I donâ€™t think we need to issue refunds or change this immediately. I can flag this to Austin for when she returns and circle back to you. Agreed that weâ€™ll need to send out a communication, and my thought is we can word it as this will be our process going forward. [01/24/2025 12:33] Closing this ticket as this issue is currently being handled by Alexis and Austin. If any further steps are taken, the associated teams will be made aware.

Thank you, Charity [06/12/2024 05:51] {color:#172B4D}We distribute approximately 180 - 220 bags each week. Our bags contain the following items:{color} {color:#172B4D} Bottled water, milk shelf stable 8oz, juice box 6-10oz, applesauce cup 4oz, tuna pouch 2oz, package of peanut butter cracker (lance)/ chips 1oz bags variety, package of cookies/granola bar, cereal in prepackaged bowl, 2 saltine packs ( 2 cracker in each pack).{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} I hope this helps. When I order it is based on need and the amount of storage space we have. Usually it is 50-60 cases of milk( 27 boxes per case), 12-18 cases of applesauce(96 cups per case), pallet or water ( 48 cases of 24 bottles per case). These items usually last 2- 3months.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} Items we get from Sckenck Foods include: 14 prepackaged cereal bowls (96 per case), 8 peanut butter cracker (12 8packs per case) , 20-30 juice boxes (motts 36 per case), 6 saltines (500 2pk) 8 cookies (120 pks per case). Trips to BJ's, Costco , Walmart and Amazon provide some of the above and also the 50 tuna (10-12 2oz pouches per box). Sometimes we even get Vienna sausages. Granted none of this is considered healthy but it is convenient and ready to eat.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} We also distribute canned goods to those who have a place to cook ( about 6-15) a week.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} Let me know if you have any questions or need anything else.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} ---- {color:#172B4D}{color} [06/14/2024 12:49] Thank you for the insight. Merged Comments: [10/24/2024 11:28] !Outlook-aw13vnk5.png|thumbnail! !Outlook-rs1fbxgg.png|thumbnail! [10/24/2024 01:31] Dr. Head, We appreciate the wonderful service you provide to your community and your partnership with CAFB for the last 15 years. Different programs within CAFB have different rules and regulations. TEFAP falls under the rules and regulations of MD DHS, collection of SDI forms is one of the requirements set forth by them not by myself or by CAFB. I completely understand that the work that you and all your volunteers do is hard and exhausting work. We also understand that not everyone is able to, qualifies for, or feels comfortable completing the SDI form. This is why we do always recommend there be non TEFAP food set aside for those do not qualify or are unable to complete the SDI form. My goal is not to suspend New Hope and Life Church of God, it is to work with you and each partner to ensure there is compliance with regulations set forth by MD DHS, to work together when other problems arise, and to get to know each partner to the best of my ability so that I can continue to advocate for change at the state level. Regarding the monthly inventory report for the month of August, like covered in the civil rights training, regardless of whether food was distributed a report must still be submitted. In the case of no distribution, you would just need to put 0 under the household and individuals served, note any inventory you have at the time, sign and submit. I can also look at your sales order record and send you the food ordered around that time frame which may help in the completion of the report. I do want to remind you that I am out of town tomorrow Friday October 24th and Monday, October 28th. Like stated in the previous emails, what needs to be submitted on Wednesday, October 23rd is the signed corrective action plan, a summary of how you will be collecting SDI forms, and submission of the monthly inventory reports that have not yet been submitted. Submission of the reports can be through the links originally sent or if your organization completed the reports previously, they should have been sent an email copy of the report which can then be emailed to me. I appreciate your patience, understanding and the work you and you organization does for the community. Best, Lucy {color:inherit} {color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:inherit}{color}

MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Hello there'¦we can do delivery Tuesday May 28th if that's ok'¦ Sent from my iPhone On May 13, 2024, at 4:10'¯PM, Partner Support wrote: ï»¿ Dear Partners, We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused. Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule. In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding. Thank you for your patience and cooperation. Sincerely, Partner Support DH Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution Capital Area Food Bank P. 571.390.9875 | F. 703.541.0179 dharmon@capitalareafoodbank.org|mailto:dharmon@capitalareafoodbank.org 4900 Puerto Rico Ave, NE Washington DC 20017 https: www.facebook.com/CapitalAreaFoodBank |https: www.facebook.com/CapitalAreaFoodBank |https: www.linkedin.com/company/capitalareafoodbank |https: twitter.com/foodbankmetrodc |https: www.instagram.com/capitalareafoodbank/ Please email all customer service questions or concerns to partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org |mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org so that one of my colleagues or I can assist you promptly. Thank you!

Summary: Good evening, I am getting a prompt to submit my organization hour reports or our account will be locked. Please advise r
Merged Comments: [10/01/2024 03:19] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called "Hours of Operations" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled "Hours of Operations." Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click "verify" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated. If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours|https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours|smart-link] Thank you, Charity

For individuals with access to multiple shopping accounts, please keep the following rules in mind: 1. You must use the logins provided below. Our system does not allow for a single account to access all your sites; each site requires a different set of credentials. 2. You cannot change the passwords listed below. 3. You will not be able to use the "forgot password" tool. If you experience any issues with your login, please contact us at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org. Because you are using the same email for logging in, clicking the "forgot password" option will affect all your other logins. Here are your credentials: - **NHT R. Charity [01/24/2025 03:51] Hello, Thank you for contacting customer support. Due to a recent update of our website, some partners may be experiencing issues with editing orders, or adding items to their cart. We are asking that if partnerâ€™s are experiencing any issues to please do a hard reset of your browser. Please clear the â€œcacheâ€ on the browser you are using and refresh the page to begin shopping again. You can either search online how to clear the cache for the specific browser you are using, or you can tell us which browser you are using and we will be happy to send you the instructions. Please note that this is necessary as the settings on our website have changed and if the cache is not clear, it will function based off of the old settings. Hope this helps, Charity

Merged Comments: [01/28/2025 01:31] Good afternoon, Mr. Oliver, I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for bringing this to our attention! I have discussed this matter with our leadership and the team involved in this initiative. We appreciate you reopening the discussion. When we initiated this plan, our goal was to alleviate the burden on our Tuesday schedule due to the number of large deliveries we have on that day. However, we acknowledge the challenges this has caused for your agency, which was not our intended outcome. Letâ€™s work together to find a solution! One option I wanted to explore with you is whether you would be open to either receiving all your food items on Fridays or accepting deliveries on Mondays instead of Tuesdays. Please let me know your preference, and if neither option works for you, I will take that information back to our department leaders and Operations for further consideration. Our aim is to ensure that we do not burden your distribution or volunteers. Thank you, Pastor Oliver! Best regards, "D" [02/03/2025 12:02] Good morning Mr. Oliver, just checking in here to see if you saw my response. [02/03/2025 12:05] Hello thanks for your follow up\! Merged Comments: [12/13/2024 09:10] Good morning, Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. You can pick up donation boxes at the food bank from Monday to Friday, 8 AM to 4 PM, at our warehouse in Washington, DC. If you arrive between 8 AM and 2 PM, please go to the side of the warehouse designated for partner pickups. If you cannot come during those hours, please visit the front of the building where our receptionist is located, and ask for donation boxes from 2 PM to 4 PM. Please note that our CAFB donation boxes cannot be used for partner donations. For example, you should not place them outside stores for accepting donations to your organization. If you are raising awareness and fundraising for your organization, please refrain from using the CAFB branded boxes. Thank you, "D"

We received 2 bins watermelon, 1 bin corn, 4 cases Halal chicken leg quarters, 20 boxes Corn Flakes and 5 sacks of lentils. The driver said he had 4 pallets for us, all of which we received. I just checked again and these are the items that are missing: 5 sacks lentils 6 cases 8-oz milk 1 box assorted green vegetables 10 cases white rice 5 cases dried pinto beans 6 cases tuna 2 cases assorted soup 10 cases red lentil Jambalaya I am sorry that I am late in reporting this. Merged Comments: [10/04/2024 02:17] Good afternoon and thank you for contacting customer support. We apologize for the inconvenience this may have caused and are working with our transportation and operation team to investigate this issue. Most of the warehouse and operations team have gone home for the weekend at this time Iâ€™ll be sure to follow up with you as soon as I receive feedback from my colleagues. CiArra [10/04/2024 02:23] Thank you, CiArra. Judy [10/07/2024 01:13] Good afternoon, CiArra. I hope you are doing well. Do you have an update on the missing pallet? I am wondering whether to try to order the same items for this Fridayâ€™s delivery. Thanks, Judy [10/09/2024 06:00] Good afternoon Judy, I hope this message finds you well. I have been working with CiArra to resolve this issue, and unfortunately, we were not able to locate your missing items in the warehouse. We sincerely apologize for this inconvenience and are taking steps to ensure it does not happen again. I have processed a credit for your agency, which will be applied to the invoice related to this order (Invoice 178408, Credit is: 8236). The credit amount for the missing items is $595.95. We are actively working to improve our delivery and fulfillment processes and appreciate your understanding and patience during this time. I have already escalated this issue to our leadership and informed them of the impact it has had on your distributions. If you need anything from us, please let us know. Once again, we apologize for this inconvenience. "D" [10/09/2024 06:16] Thank you, "D". I appreciate your help. Judy [10/09/2024 06:17] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Good morning. Could you please identify what kind of winter squash is in the bin? The butternut squash have been way too big for most of our families to handle. Thanks, Judy
Merged Comments: [11/07/2024 10:34] Good afternoon, Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. After speaking with our Head of Procurement, he clarified that there can sometimes be a mix of winter squash, but he believes this one is butternut squash. Thank you, "D" [11/07/2024 10:38] Thank you, "D". I did end up deleting this one from our shopping cart because the butternut squash is too big for many of our guests and our volunteers to handle. If there is any way to provide more detail about the produce offerings it would be really helpful. Judy [11/07/2024 10:58] Hi Judy! Yes, we are collaborating with our internal teams to provide additional details about the items when they arrive at the food bank, and we are also ensuring that there are photos included. For some of our produce, the descriptions can be broader, and when items are received, they may be mixed. For example, we might receive potatoes, but three bins could contain one type, while the other four contain a different type, and they are all categorized simply as potatoes. We are definitely working on improving descriptions to enhance the overall experience. Best, "D"

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: I just wanted to bring to your attention that the weight listed for two bulk produce items, potatoes/onions and cabbage, is doubled. The quantity of items is not doubled so it probably doesn't make a difference for this delivery, but it would in the future when CAFB initiates its rationing of produce.
Merged Comments: [11/20/2024 02:55] Good afternoon, Thank you so much for your feedback; we truly appreciate it! I reached out to one of our managers in the ERP team, and she informed me that they are aware of this issue and are working to resolve it by tomorrow. The weights in the shopping carts and your total weights are accurate, but the line weight calculation is currently incorrect and will be fixed soon. This information is very helpful, and I appreciate you bringing it to our attention. Rest assured, this will be resolved by the time we begin our new product allocation process. Best regards, "D"

Gladys Reid On Friday, September 13, 2024, 3:35 PM, Customer Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) wrote: Good afternoon Partners, If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use. Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: Get Help Map|https: www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/ . To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on September 19th from 9 am to 10 am . These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to register |https: forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations. Thank you, The Customer Relations Team } } } ,"attrs": }

Charity [08/14/2024 12:53] {color:#172B4D}Hi Charity,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} I was unable to print the pdf of the order because it never showed. When I put in the order for the 5 cases of catfish, there were only 5 cases available. I requested the last 5 cases but, 10 cases which showed in the cart when only 5 were available. I saved the order, but no pdf of the order showed to allow me to print.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} An error message showed to change and when I did the cart was empty. When I went back to retrieve the 5 cases, they were gone. Therefore, I wasn't able to get the item # for the catfish.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} {color:#172B4D} Toni Gaines{color} {color:#172B4D} Our Lady of Perpetual Help Church{color} {color:#172B4D} 301-222-7285{color} ---- {color:#172B4D}{color} [08/14/2024 03:43] Hi Toni, Please note that even if an item is in your cart, items do not hold. There is a chance the catfish could have been purchased while you were ordering, changing the total quantity available. I believe this is what happened with you. We apologize that you were not able to purchase the catfish as our products are available on first come first serve basis. Please let me know if I can be of further assistance. Charity [08/14/2024 04:12] {color:#333333} Hi Charity, I'm aware that items are on a first come first serve basis. However, the items were in the cart. I saved the cart and it showed 10 items in the cart when I only ordered the 5 items available. This is when the pdf of the order did not appear for me to download. The screen had an error message instead stating the 10 items were not available, but I only ordered 5 which were available. Can we be put on a waiting list should you get more catfish? Thanks for your response. Toni Gaines{color}{color:#575757}{color} {color:#333333}{color} [08/14/2024 04:12] Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved. [08/16/2024 11:39] Hi Toni, We appreciate your patience as we look into this issue. Can you please confirm if this was a TEFAP product or not? Charity [08/16/2024 11:44] Hi Charity, Yes, the catfish was a TEFAP product. Thanks, Toni Gaines Our Lady of Perpetual Help Church{color:#575757}{color} [08/16/2024 01:49] Good afternoon, Â We contacted the TEFAP Team and learned that we anticipate receiving a shipment of catfish between October 16th and 31st. Currently, we do not have a waitlist or a reminder system linked to our inventory to alert partners when items are back in stock. This is feedback we have received from partners and have conveyed to our Food Resourcing and Inventory Teams for consideration. Â If you wish to check back during that time and do not see the catfish available, we would be happy to reach out to the TEFAP team to confirm if the shipment is still expected during that period. It seems that in your original order, the product went out of stock. Our inventory is live and operates on a first-come, first-served basis as you know. At times, items may be taken by the time you start the checkout process, resulting in an error message prompting you to update your item quantities based on what's available. Â Additionally, there may be different lots of items with varying expiration dates. Consequently, you may have two lots of the same product arriving at different times, with one having a later expiration date than the other. Depending on the date of your order, the item may have gone out of stock for the specific case lot you selected, even though there are still some available on the menu. This occurs due to the date you chose for your order. Â We acknowledge that our inventory system is complex and are striving to make it more user-friendly and accessible for partners to obtain information from the website. Â Thank you, Customer Relations

Description:
MAIN CONTENT:
MAIN CONTENT: MAIN CONTENT: Our organization is scheduled for our next food distribution on Monday 01/06, but when I go to schedule the delivery this date is unavailable. Is this an error, or is the food bank closed that week? Thank you!
Merged Comments: [01/02/2025 12:11] Good morning! I hope you are doing well. Happy New Year! Since we were closed from December 25th until January 2nd, the last day to place an order for January 6th was December 24th, in accordance with our three business day fulfillment rule. This is why you were unable to make an order for January 6th, and we sincerely apologize for any inconvenience. Please note that anytime a day is marked in gray on the calendar, it either means that the calendar is full or the day is no longer available due to the deadline for placing an order having passed. You can schedule a delivery or pickup for Tuesday, January 7th, until the end of the day on January 3rd. There are still some slots available, so please take a look soon to secure an available time. Thank you, "D"
